{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1243,"text":"I want to share some personal friends and stories with you"},{"time":5195,"text":"that I've actually never talked about in public before"},{"time":7232,"text":"to help illustrate the idea"},{"time":9592,"text":"and the need and the hope"},{"time":11511,"text":"for us to reinvent our health care system around the world."},{"time":14793,"text":"Twenty-four years ago, I had -- a sophomore in college,"},{"time":18180,"text":"I had a series of fainting spells. No alcohol was involved."},{"time":21002,"text":"And I ended up in student health,"},{"time":23933,"text":"and they ran some labwork and came back right away,"},{"time":26102,"text":"and said, \"Kidney problems.\""},{"time":28275,"text":"And before I knew it, I was involved and thrown into"},{"time":31725,"text":"this six months of tests and trials and tribulations"},{"time":34945,"text":"with six doctors across two hospitals"},{"time":37629,"text":"in this clash of medical titans"},{"time":40325,"text":"to figure out which one of them was right"},{"time":42369,"text":"about what was wrong with me."},{"time":44833,"text":"And I'm sitting in a waiting room some time later for an ultrasound,"},{"time":48106,"text":"and all six of these doctors actually show up in the room at once,"},{"time":50929,"text":"and I'm like, \"Uh oh, this is bad news.\""},{"time":55281,"text":"And their diagnosis was this:"},{"time":56844,"text":"They said, \"You have two rare kidney diseases"},{"time":58754,"text":"that are going to actually destroy your kidneys eventually,"},{"time":61435,"text":"you have cancer-like cells in your immune system"},{"time":63972,"text":"that we need to start treatment right away,"},{"time":65889,"text":"and you'll never be eligible for a kidney transplant,"},{"time":68346,"text":"and you're not likely to live more than two or three years.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":71765,"text":"Now, with the gravity of this doomsday diagnosis,"},{"time":74729,"text":"it just sucked me in immediately,"},{"time":77129,"text":"as if I began preparing myself as a patient"},{"time":79771,"text":"to die according to the schedule that they had just given to me,"},{"time":83868,"text":"until I met a patient named Verna in a waiting room,"},{"time":86508,"text":"who became a dear friend, and she grabbed me one day"},{"time":88566,"text":"and took me off to the medical library"},{"time":90560,"text":"and did a bunch of research on these diagnoses and these diseases,"},{"time":93494,"text":"and said, \"Eric, these people who get this"},{"time":96014,"text":"are normally in their '70s and '80s."},{"time":97962,"text":"They don't know anything about you. Wake up."},{"time":101073,"text":"Take control of your health and get on with your life.\""},{"time":104195,"text":"And I did."}]},{"cues":[{"time":105737,"text":"Now, these people making these proclamations to me"},{"time":108097,"text":"were not bad people."},{"time":109423,"text":"In fact, these professionals were miracle workers,"},{"time":111984,"text":"but they're working in a flawed, expensive system that's set up the wrong way."},{"time":116050,"text":"It's dependent on hospitals and clinics for our every care need."},{"time":119305,"text":"It's dependent on specialists who just look at parts of us."},{"time":122972,"text":"It's dependent on guesswork of diagnoses and drug cocktails,"},{"time":126887,"text":"and so something either works or you die."},{"time":129487,"text":"And it's dependent on passive patients"},{"time":133695,"text":"who just take it and don't ask any questions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":137457,"text":"Now the problem with this model"},{"time":139019,"text":"is that it's unsustainable globally."},{"time":141505,"text":"It's unaffordable globally."},{"time":143459,"text":"We need to invent what I call a personal health system."},{"time":146946,"text":"So what does this personal health system look like,"},{"time":149269,"text":"and what new technologies and roles is it going to entail?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":154310,"text":"Now, I'm going to start by actually sharing with you"},{"time":156463,"text":"a new friend of mine, Libby,"},{"time":158359,"text":"somebody I've become quite attached to over the last six months."},{"time":161073,"text":"This is Libby, or actually, this is an ultrasound image of Libby."},{"time":164949,"text":"This is the kidney transplant I was never supposed to have."},{"time":167820,"text":"Now, this is an image that we shot a couple of weeks ago for today,"},{"time":171671,"text":"and you'll notice, on the edge of this image,"},{"time":173611,"text":"there's some dark spots there, which was really concerning to me."},{"time":176520,"text":"So we're going to actually do a live exam"},{"time":179049,"text":"to sort of see how Libby's doing."},{"time":180424,"text":"This is not a wardrobe malfunction. I have to take my belt off here."},{"time":183142,"text":"Don't you in the front row worry or anything."},{"time":185276,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":186558,"text":"I'm going to use a device from a company called Mobisante."},{"time":190285,"text":"This is a portable ultrasound."},{"time":191759,"text":"It can plug into a smartphone. It can plug into a tablet."},{"time":194302,"text":"Mobisante is up in Redmond, Washington,"},{"time":196432,"text":"and they kindly trained me to actually do this on myself."},{"time":200082,"text":"They're not approved to do this. Patients are not approved to do this."},{"time":202287,"text":"This is a concept demo, so I want to make that clear."},{"time":205098,"text":"All right, I gotta gel up."},{"time":206185,"text":"Now the people in the front row are very nervous. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":210636,"text":"And I want to actually introduce you to Dr. Batiuk,"},{"time":214681,"text":"who's another friend of mine."},{"time":216128,"text":"He's up in Legacy Good Samaritan Hospital in Portland, Oregon."},{"time":220014,"text":"So let me just make sure. Hey, Dr. Batiuk. Can you hear me okay?"},{"time":223508,"text":"And actually, can you see Libby?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":225684,"text":"Thomas Batuik: Hi there, Eric."},{"time":226862,"text":"You look busy. How are you?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":228107,"text":"Eric Dishman: I'm good. I'm just taking my clothes off"},{"time":230835,"text":"in front of a few hundred people. It's wonderful."},{"time":233404,"text":"So I just wanted to see, is this the image you need to get?"},{"time":238061,"text":"And I know you want to look and see if those spots are still there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241798,"text":"TB: Okay. Well let's scan around a little bit here,"},{"time":244527,"text":"give me a lay of the land."}]},{"cues":[{"time":245802,"text":"ED: All right.TB: Okay. Turn it a little bit inside,"},{"time":249318,"text":"a little bit toward the middle for me."},{"time":251718,"text":"Okay, that's good. How about up a little bit?"},{"time":256514,"text":"Okay, freeze that image. That's a good one for me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":259564,"text":"ED: All right. Now last week, when I did this,"},{"time":262251,"text":"you had me measure that spot to the right."},{"time":265052,"text":"Should I do that again?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":266739,"text":"TB: Yeah, let's do that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":267783,"text":"ED: All right. This is kind of hard to do"},{"time":271087,"text":"with one hand on your belly and one hand on measuring,"},{"time":273258,"text":"but I've got it, I think,"},{"time":274513,"text":"and I'll save that image and send it to you."},{"time":277064,"text":"So tell me a little bit about what this dark spot means."},{"time":279536,"text":"It's not something I was very happy about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":281641,"text":"TB: Many people after a kidney transplant"},{"time":283584,"text":"will develop a little fluid collection around the kidney."},{"time":286852,"text":"Most of the time it doesn't create any kind of mischief,"},{"time":290133,"text":"but it does warrant looking at,"},{"time":292541,"text":"so I'm happy we've got an opportunity to look at it today,"},{"time":295516,"text":"make sure that it's not growing, it's not creating any problems."},{"time":298444,"text":"Based on the other images we have,"},{"time":300660,"text":"I'm really happy how it looks today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":303044,"text":"ED: All right. Well, I guess we'll double check it when I come in."},{"time":305441,"text":"I've got my six month biopsy in a couple of weeks,"},{"time":308006,"text":"and I'm going to let you do that in the clinic,"},{"time":309715,"text":"because I don't think I can do that one on myself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":312155,"text":"TB: Good choice.ED: All right, thanks, Dr. Batiuk."},{"time":314800,"text":"All right. So what you're sort of seeing here"},{"time":316931,"text":"is an example of disruptive technologies,"},{"time":319039,"text":"of mobile, social and analytic technologies."},{"time":322235,"text":"These are the foundations of what's going to make personal health possible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":325146,"text":"Now there's really three pillars"},{"time":327731,"text":"of this personal health I want to talk to you about now,"},{"time":329628,"text":"and it's care anywhere, care networking and care customization."},{"time":333420,"text":"And you just saw a little bit of the first two"},{"time":335103,"text":"with my interaction with Dr. Batiuk."}]},{"cues":[{"time":336644,"text":"So let's start with care anywhere."},{"time":339524,"text":"Humans invented the idea of hospitals and clinics"},{"time":342252,"text":"in the 1780s. It is time to update our thinking."},{"time":346152,"text":"We have got to untether clinicians and patients"},{"time":349646,"text":"from the notion of traveling to a special"},{"time":352264,"text":"bricks-and-mortar place for all of our care,"},{"time":354844,"text":"because these places are often the wrong tool,"},{"time":357145,"text":"and the most expensive tool, for the job."},{"time":359611,"text":"And these are sometimes unsafe places to send our sickest patients,"},{"time":363163,"text":"especially in an era of superbugs"},{"time":365300,"text":"and hospital-acquired infections."},{"time":367416,"text":"And many countries are going to go brickless from the start"},{"time":370298,"text":"because they're never going to be able to afford"},{"time":372264,"text":"the mega-medicalplexes that a lot of the rest of the world has built."},{"time":376784,"text":"Now I personally learned that hospitals"},{"time":379540,"text":"can be a very dangerous place at a young age."},{"time":382056,"text":"This was me in third grade."},{"time":383896,"text":"I broke my elbow very seriously, had to have surgery,"},{"time":386312,"text":"worried that they were going to actually lose the arm."},{"time":388639,"text":"Recovering from the surgery in the hospital, I get bedsores."},{"time":391575,"text":"Those bedsores become infected,"},{"time":393808,"text":"and they give me an antibiotic which I end up being allergic to,"},{"time":396744,"text":"and now my whole body breaks out,"},{"time":398695,"text":"and now all of those become infected."},{"time":401255,"text":"The longer I stayed in the hospital, the sicker I became,"},{"time":403802,"text":"and the more expensive it became,"},{"time":405387,"text":"and this happens to millions of people around the world every year."},{"time":408732,"text":"The future of personal health that I'm talking about"},{"time":411075,"text":"says care must occur at home as the default model,"},{"time":415533,"text":"not in a hospital or clinic."},{"time":417013,"text":"You have to earn your way into those places"},{"time":418573,"text":"by being sick enough to use that tool for the job."},{"time":422139,"text":"Now the smartphones that we're already carrying"},{"time":424245,"text":"can clearly have diagnostic devices like ultrasounds plugged into them,"},{"time":427971,"text":"and a whole array of others, today,"},{"time":430142,"text":"and as sensing is built into these,"},{"time":431664,"text":"we'll be able to do vital signs monitor"},{"time":433694,"text":"and behavioral monitoring like we've never had before."},{"time":436533,"text":"Many of us will have implantables that will actually look"},{"time":439085,"text":"real-time at what's going on with our blood chemistry"},{"time":441822,"text":"and in our proteins right now."},{"time":444069,"text":"Now the software is also getting smarter, right?"},{"time":446764,"text":"Think about a coach, an agent online,"},{"time":449861,"text":"that's going to help me do safe self-care."},{"time":451997,"text":"That same interaction that we just did with the ultrasound"},{"time":454302,"text":"will likely have real-time image processing,"},{"time":456525,"text":"and the device will say, \"Up, down, left, right,"},{"time":458670,"text":"ah, Eric, that's the perfect spot to send that image"},{"time":461326,"text":"off to your doctor.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":463175,"text":"Now, if we've got all these networked devices"},{"time":465382,"text":"that are helping us to do care anywhere,"},{"time":467762,"text":"it stands to reason that we also need a team"},{"time":469557,"text":"to be able to interact with all of that stuff,"},{"time":471544,"text":"and that leads to the second pillar I want to talk about,"},{"time":474165,"text":"care networking."},{"time":475737,"text":"We have got to go beyond this paradigm"},{"time":478883,"text":"of isolated specialists doing parts care"},{"time":482534,"text":"to multidisciplinary teams doing person care."},{"time":486753,"text":"Uncoordinated care today is expensive at best,"},{"time":490149,"text":"and it is deadly at worst."},{"time":492244,"text":"Eighty percent of medical errors are actually caused"},{"time":494647,"text":"by communication and coordination problems"},{"time":496595,"text":"amongst medical team members."},{"time":498916,"text":"I had my own heart scare years ago in graduate school,"},{"time":501155,"text":"when we're under treatment for the kidney,"},{"time":503269,"text":"and suddenly, they're like, \"Oh, we think you have a heart problem.\""},{"time":505883,"text":"And I have these palpitations that are showing up."},{"time":507768,"text":"They put me through five weeks of tests --"},{"time":510274,"text":"very expensive, very scary -- before the nurse finally notices"},{"time":513773,"text":"the piece of the paper, my meds list"},{"time":515869,"text":"that I've been carrying to every single appointment,"},{"time":517391,"text":"and says, \"Oh my gosh.\""},{"time":519577,"text":"Three different specialists had prescribed"},{"time":521546,"text":"three different versions of the same drug to me."},{"time":523585,"text":"I did not have a heart problem. I had an overdose problem."},{"time":527860,"text":"I had a care coordination problem."},{"time":530673,"text":"And this happens to millions of people every year."},{"time":533439,"text":"I want to use technology that we're all working on and making happen"},{"time":537073,"text":"to make health care a coordinated team sport."},{"time":540805,"text":"Now this is the most frightening thing to me."},{"time":543107,"text":"Out of all the care I've had in hospitals and clinics around the world,"},{"time":547365,"text":"the first time I've ever had a true team-based care experience"},{"time":550712,"text":"was at Legacy Good Sam these last six months"},{"time":553483,"text":"for me to go get this."},{"time":554541,"text":"And this is a picture of my graduation team from Legacy."},{"time":557510,"text":"There's a couple of the folks here. You'll recognize Dr. Batiuk."},{"time":560020,"text":"We just talked to him. Here's Jenny, one of the nurses,"},{"time":562636,"text":"Allison, who helped manage the transplant list,"},{"time":564948,"text":"and a dozen other people who aren't pictured,"},{"time":567092,"text":"a pharmacist, a psychologist, a nutritionist,"},{"time":569628,"text":"even a financial counselor, Lisa,"},{"time":571870,"text":"who helped us deal with all the insurance hassles."},{"time":574597,"text":"I wept the day I graduated."},{"time":577196,"text":"I should have been happy, because I was so well"},{"time":578823,"text":"that I could go back to my normal doctors,"},{"time":580476,"text":"but I wept because I was so actually connected to this team."}]},{"cues":[{"time":583771,"text":"And here's the most important part."},{"time":585367,"text":"The other people in this picture are me and my wife, Ashley."},{"time":588406,"text":"Legacy trained us on how to do care for me at home"},{"time":592508,"text":"so that they could offload the hospitals and clinics."},{"time":595252,"text":"That's the only way that the model works."},{"time":597716,"text":"My team is actually working in China"},{"time":599532,"text":"on one of these self-care models"},{"time":601271,"text":"for a project we called Age-Friendly Cities."},{"time":603644,"text":"We're trying to help build a social network"},{"time":605438,"text":"that can help track and train the care of seniors"},{"time":607922,"text":"caring for themselves"},{"time":609429,"text":"as well as the care provided by their family members"},{"time":611834,"text":"or volunteer community health workers,"},{"time":614316,"text":"as well as have an exchange network online,"},{"time":616572,"text":"where, for example, I can donate three hours of care a day to your mom,"},{"time":619900,"text":"if somebody else can help me with transportation to meals,"},{"time":622770,"text":"and we exchange all of that online."},{"time":625428,"text":"The most important point I want to make to you about this"},{"time":627818,"text":"is the sacred and somewhat over-romanticized"},{"time":631132,"text":"doctor-patient one-on-one"},{"time":633906,"text":"is a relic of the past."},{"time":636022,"text":"The future of health care is smart teams,"},{"time":638474,"text":"and you'd better be on that team for yourself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":642043,"text":"Now, the last thing that I want to talk to you about"},{"time":644335,"text":"is care customization,"},{"time":645575,"text":"because if you've got care anywhere and you've got care networking,"},{"time":648500,"text":"those are going to go a long way towards improving our health care system,"},{"time":651308,"text":"but there's still too much guesswork."},{"time":654341,"text":"Randomized clinical trials were actually invented in 1948"},{"time":658429,"text":"to help invent the drugs that cured tuberculosis,"},{"time":661811,"text":"and those are important things, don't get me wrong."},{"time":664108,"text":"These population studies that we've done have created"},{"time":665973,"text":"tons of miracle drugs that have saved millions of lives,"},{"time":668552,"text":"but the problem is that health care"},{"time":670987,"text":"is treating us as averages, not unique individuals,"},{"time":675067,"text":"because at the end of the day,"},{"time":676614,"text":"the patient is not the same thing as the population"},{"time":679869,"text":"who are studied. That's what's leading to the guesswork."},{"time":683147,"text":"The technologies that are coming,"},{"time":684985,"text":"high-performance computing, analytics,"},{"time":687074,"text":"big data that everyone's talking about,"},{"time":688991,"text":"will allow us to build predictive models for each of us"},{"time":691910,"text":"as individual patients."},{"time":693864,"text":"And the magic here is, experiment on my avatar"},{"time":698323,"text":"in software, not my body in suffering."}]},{"cues":[{"time":703124,"text":"Now, I've had two examples I want to quickly share with you"},{"time":705607,"text":"of this kind of care customization on my own journey."},{"time":708166,"text":"The first was quite simple. I finally realized some years ago"},{"time":711343,"text":"that all my medical teams were optimizing my treatment for longevity."},{"time":715220,"text":"It's like a badge of honor to see how long they can get the patient to live."},{"time":717974,"text":"I was optimizing my life for quality of life,"},{"time":721041,"text":"and quality of life for me means time in snow."},{"time":725421,"text":"So on my chart, I forced them to put, \"Patient goal:"},{"time":728251,"text":"low doses of drugs over longer periods of time,"},{"time":732017,"text":"side effects friendly to skiing.\""},{"time":735263,"text":"And I think that's why I achieved longevity."},{"time":737915,"text":"I think that time-in-snow therapy was as important"},{"time":740147,"text":"as the pharmaceuticals that I had."},{"time":742280,"text":"Now the second example of customization -- and by the way,"},{"time":744595,"text":"you can't customize care if you don't know your own goals,"},{"time":746491,"text":"so health care can't know those until you know your own health care goals."},{"time":749860,"text":"But the second example I want to give you is,"},{"time":751572,"text":"I happened to be an early guinea pig,"},{"time":753359,"text":"and I got very lucky to have my whole genome sequenced."},{"time":756963,"text":"Now it took about two weeks of processing"},{"time":759285,"text":"on Intel's highest-end servers to make this happen,"},{"time":761409,"text":"and another six months of human and computing labor"},{"time":764441,"text":"to make sense of all of that data."},{"time":767003,"text":"And at the end of all of that, they said, \"Yes,"},{"time":770053,"text":"those diagnoses of that clash of medical titans"},{"time":772491,"text":"all of those years ago were wrong,"},{"time":774875,"text":"and we have a better path forward.\""},{"time":777149,"text":"The future that Intel's working on now is to figure out"},{"time":779534,"text":"how to make that computing for personalized medicine"},{"time":781731,"text":"go from months and weeks to even hours,"},{"time":785484,"text":"and make this kind of tool available,"},{"time":787155,"text":"not just in the mainframes of tier-one research hospitals around the world,"},{"time":790973,"text":"but in the mainstream -- every patient, every clinic"},{"time":793779,"text":"with access to whole genome sequencing."},{"time":795928,"text":"And I tell you, this kind of care customization"},{"time":798271,"text":"for everything from your goals to your genetics"},{"time":801097,"text":"will be the most game-changing transformation"},{"time":802862,"text":"that we witness in health care during our lifetime."}]},{"cues":[{"time":806444,"text":"So these three pillars of personal health,"},{"time":809378,"text":"care anywhere, care networking, care customization,"},{"time":812236,"text":"are happening in pieces now,"},{"time":813483,"text":"but this vision will completely fail if we don't step up"},{"time":817266,"text":"as caregivers and as patients to take on new roles."},{"time":821267,"text":"It's what my friend Verna said:"},{"time":822920,"text":"Wake up and take control of your health."},{"time":825041,"text":"Because at the end of the day these technologies"},{"time":826630,"text":"are simply about people caring for other people"},{"time":830527,"text":"and ourselves in some powerful new ways."}]},{"cues":[{"time":833938,"text":"And it's in that spirit that I want to introduce you"},{"time":835498,"text":"to one last friend, very quickly."},{"time":838049,"text":"Tracey Gamley stepped up to give me the impossible kidney"},{"time":841916,"text":"that I was never supposed to have."}]},{"cues":[{"time":846597,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":862992,"text":"So Tracey, just tell us a little bit quickly about what the donor experience was like with you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":867349,"text":"Tracey Gamley: For me, it was really easy."},{"time":869233,"text":"I only had one night in the hospital."},{"time":871184,"text":"The surgery was done laparoscopically,"},{"time":872888,"text":"so I have just five very small scars on my abdomen,"},{"time":876094,"text":"and I had four weeks away from work"},{"time":878133,"text":"and went back to doing everything I'd done before"},{"time":880016,"text":"without any changes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":881532,"text":"ED: Well, I probably will never get a chance to say this to you"},{"time":884518,"text":"in such a large audience ever again."},{"time":886977,"text":"So \"thank you\" feel likes a really trite word,"},{"time":889764,"text":"but thank you from the bottom of my heart for saving my life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":892226,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":898109,"text":"This TED stage and all of the TED stages"},{"time":900558,"text":"are often about celebrating innovation"},{"time":903284,"text":"and celebrating new technologies,"},{"time":904393,"text":"and I've done that here today,"},{"time":906678,"text":"and I've seen amazing things coming from TED speakers,"},{"time":909007,"text":"I mean, my gosh, artificial kidneys, even printable kidneys, that are coming."},{"time":913040,"text":"But until such time that these amazing technologies"},{"time":916221,"text":"are available to all of us, and even when they are,"},{"time":919259,"text":"it's up to us to care for, and even save, one another."},{"time":923686,"text":"I hope you will go out and make personal health happen"},{"time":926124,"text":"for yourselves and for everyone. Thanks so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":930052,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}